        <abstract>
            <para>During  1999-2011 in Kherson were published Scientific Readings. This Scientific readings initiated and organised by Kherson State University. It was established to devote to the issues of environmental ecology, human, plant, animal ecology, ecological culture and environmental education. Problems of biodiversity conservation and development in Ukraine and Europe are discussed.
The Scientific readings is regional and contains materials mainly by specialists from scientific and educational institutions of the Kherson Region. All articles are recommended to be published by the decisions of the Kherson State University. The conference is held in the spring in odd-numbered years (1999, 2001, 2003, 2005, 2007, 2009) etc. The data set contain information of 2005, 2007, 2009 and 2011 scientific articles.
The Scientific readings is not publicized in any digital library of scientific literature and as of 2024 it is not available in any digital library of scientific literature. Nonetheless, the publication contains important scientific information about the occurrences of animal and plant species, including unique records of endemic and protected species of southern Ukraine.
The articles of this proceeding highlight the problems of environmental ecology, human, plant, animal ecology, ecological culture and environmental education. 
The dataset contains an comprehensive records of all species occurrences that have been published in scientific readings  “Faltzfein readings” The nomenclature of the dataset follows original taxa names.
The materials in Scientific readings are especially important in light of the events of 2022, when a Russian full scale invasion. The data from these Scientific readings actually document the historical state of biodiversity before the outbreak of a full-scale invasion war in the southern Ukraine.</para>
        </abstract>
